<p align="left">This allows <?echo stripslashes($config_values['TITLE']);?> to schedule the start and stopping of campaign. Give it a name of a queue (this is not the same as the asterisk queues, so really anything can go here), and a description. Give it a start and stop time. Once you've done this, the campaign will run between those times of the day.</p>
<p align="left">Note: this is setting when <?echo stripslashes($config_values['TITLE']);?> should act on the information. It will take a while to get the campaign running at full speed and it can take a while for the campaign to finish. </p>
